ermining the course of French literature up to the 1850's.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAlienation (Social psychology)vFiction. 0aAlienation (Social psychology)xFiction. 0aFrench fictionxTranslations into Englishx18th century. 0aFrench fictionxTranslations into Englishx19th century. 0aFrench fictiony18th centuryvTranslations into English. 0aFrench fictiony19th centuryvTranslations into English. 0aLove stories, FrenchxTranslations into Englishx19th century. 0aRomance fiction, Frenchy19th centuryvTranslations into English. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aalienation.  aaristocracy.  acatholic missionary.  acatholicism.  achristianity.  aclassics.  aconvent.  aconversion.  adisplacement.  aex pat.  afaith.  afrance.  afrench literature.  afrench romanticism.  agenius of christianity.  ahermit.  aincest.  aisolation.  aliterature.  amal du siecle.  amission.  amissionary.  anative american.  anature.  anoble savage.  aoutcast.  apassion.  apriest.  arace.  areligion.  areservation.  arevolution.  aromantic hero.  aromanticism.  asentimentalism.  asocial issues.  asociety.  asolitude.  asuicide.  awilderness.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052090481140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520904811423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520904811/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles